description: From Middle English straungely (“strangely, aloofly, intricately”); equivalent to strange +‎ -ly.

adverbs.description: strangely (comparative more strangely, superlative most strangely)

entries.meaning: In a strange or coincidental manner.
examples: Though I'd never gone to Boston before, everything looked strangely familiar.
Daniel was walking strangely because he had twisted his ankle.
